text: Agnieszka Roma Radwańska (born 6 March 1989 in Kraków) is a former Polish tennis player. In 2007, Radwańska became the first Polish player to win a WTA singles title. In 2012 she lost the final of the Wimbledon Championships to Serena Williams. She won WTA Finals in Singapour in 2015. ==References== ==Other websites== * * * * * Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Female tennis players Category:Sportspeople from Kraków Category:Polish tennis players
